     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>TO HIS ESTEEMED LO<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>VING FRIEND <hi>IAMES DAY,</hi> in Commendation of his Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <seg rend="decorInit">T</seg>Hy shining workes <hi>(O DAY)</hi> doe seeme so bright,</l>
      <l>Surely Thou'lt have an ever lasting light;</l>
      <l>If these thy radient beames breake forth so soone,</l>
      <l>How glorious will thy splendor be at noone:</l>
      <l>Tis but thy morning, yet thy Sunne displayes</l>
      <l>His beauty, and sends downe his golden rayes,</l>
      <l>Well <hi>(DAY)</hi> Ile tell thee this; though envy spight</l>
      <l>And Critickes snarle, thou'lt never have a night.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>T. I.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
